description: This column is a unique identifier for each delivery record in the e-commerce or online retail system. It typically contains numerical or alphanumeric values that distinguish one delivery entry from another within the 'Delivery' table.

This column is about the unique identifier assigned to each order in the e-commerce or online retail system. It is used to distinguish each order and track its details, including the products purchased, the user who placed the order, and the order status.
This column is about storing the name that appears on the credit or debit card used for an order in the e-commerce or online retail system.

This column contains information related to the full card details used for a transaction in an e-commerce or online retail system. It typically includes the card number and other sensitive payment information required for processing orders.

This column is about the expiration date of the credit card used for making the purchase. It stores the month and year when the credit card will expire, ensuring that the transaction can be validated and processed within the valid period of the card.
This column contains the Card Verification Value (CVV) code of the customer's credit card used for verifying and authorizing online transactions within the e-commerce or online retail system.

description: This column is about storing the address details of the customer who placed the order in the e-commerce or online retail system.

This column stores the name of the city where the order is to be delivered. It is part of the shipping address information provided by the customer during the checkout process in the e-commerce or online retail system.

This column is about the state or province information associated with the delivery address of an order in the e-commerce or online retail system. It helps to determine the location for shipping purposes.
This column contains the zip code of the shipping address for an order in the e-commerce or online retail system.

This column stores the last four digits of a user's credit card. It is used for transaction verification and providing users with a partial reference to their stored payment method while maintaining security and privacy.

This column is a unique identifier for each product in the e-commerce system. It typically contains an integer value that serves as the primary key for the product and helps in distinguishing each product within the database.

Fitness Tracker with Heart Rate Monitor
description: This column is about the name of the product in the e-commerce or online retail system. It is a textual representation and typically contains a unique, user-friendly name that identifies each product.

This column is about storing the URL of the image associated with a product. It contains strings that point to the location of product images, which are used for visual representation on the e-commerce platform.

description: This column contains textual information that provides details about a specific product within the e-commerce system. It includes descriptions such as features, specifications, usage instructions, and other relevant information that helps users understand what the product is and what it offers.

This column is about storing the unique identifier (ID) of a product in the ProductRelation table within an e-commerce or online retail system. It is used to establish relationships between different products, such as related items, variations, or complementary products.
This column is about the unique identifier for each user in the e-commerce or online retail system. It typically contains an integer or a UUID that uniquely distinguishes one user from another.

This column is about storing the names of users within the e-commerce or online retail system. It contains the full names or usernames of individuals who have registered or created accounts on the platform.
